node.text:
The Padrón Family will release a preview of its most recent addition to the Family Reserve Series at the 2021 PCA show next week.

Named the No. 95, this new cigar will be offered as a PCA exclusive and only available to show attendees.

The Family Reserve line, crafted using refined and aged tobacco, is blended to create an exceptionally smooth, complex, balanced and full-bodied flavor. 

As is our tradition, the No. 95 signifies a meaningful family date honoring José Orlando Padrón's birthday; this past June 10th would have been our founding patriarch's 95th.

The release, unlike others in this box pressed series, is round, and sized at 60 x 4 3/4”. Available in both natural and maduro.
